@astroeringrand @nj_tierney @kara_woo TIPS: If you restart #rstats often and you want to limit these to appear at most once an hour, do:

> startup::install()

Then put these quoting calls in a file:

~/.Rprofile.d/quotes,interactive=TRUE,when=hourly.R

That's it

Now I realized how this was rather cavalier, especially without context (which I briefly explained here). My intent was not to diminish the great achievements of a few people in the #rstats spatial world (they will recognize themselves), but… 13/

My background is in movement ecology — that sets up the scene, and certainly explains my biases and shortcomings. I have been working primarily in #rstats for almost 20 years, rapidly working with #adehabitat and then #sp to solve spatial ecology problems. 2/

Without a second thought, I contacted all movement experts I know and suggested the idea of the #rstats Spatial Working Group (RSWG), basically scaling up a need from the movement world. This ended up as a public discussion on r-spatial on GitHub: 12/

https://t.co/2Y0R0G3uFt

With time, I contributed to a growing ecosystem, through my involvement in #adehabitatHS, or my own packages #hab or #rpostgis. I have been amazed by the progress and flourishing development of spatial #rstats packages, but also frustrated at times. 3/

https://t.co/kqgCO4Wl75

With all this said, back to my initial tweet, and the proposition to start a #rstats Spatial Working Group within the @RConsortium. My own experience within the movement world showed me a lack of shared governance and directions within our community (again, movement). 10/

So it seems I caused a few unexpected waves that may be a bit too high for me. I recently contacted a bunch of #movement experts about the idea of an #rstats Spatial Working Group within the @RConsortium, and now would be a good time to explain. A thread. 1/ https://t.co/TydLTAXBCK

1) @rocio_joo led a review of #rstats packages for tracking data (x, y, z, t). We listed and described 58 R tracking packages (as of August 2018) explicitly developed to either create/transform/analyze tracking data. 5/
